<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01911</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING SECTIONS 38, 39 AND 40 OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 4566 OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE CONTRACTORSâ€™ LICENSE LAW</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to rectify existing infirmities in R.A.No.4566, as amended by P.D.No.1746 which provides that no
contractor shall engage in the business of contracting without first having secured a Phil. Contractors 
Accreditation Board (PCAB) license to conduct business.

Seeks to propose several amendments among others such as: a) Violation shall be penalized with a fine of not less than P50,000.00 where the cost of the project is not more than P500,000,000.00; and a fine of not less than P500,000.00 where the cost of the project is more than P500,000,000.00; b) The bidder shall be automatically disqualified for award of contract; c) Higher fees for licensing, registration of application, and renewal shall be implemented: P5,000.00 for an original license; P6,000.00 for examination of an applicant; P5,000.00 for annual renewal.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GONZALES, AURELIO &quot;DONG&quot; JR. D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2019-11-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO CIVIL SERVICE AND PROFESSIONAL REGULATION on 2019-07-24;</td></tr></table>